description.narrative: The project will help achieve the following objectives: (i) Improve the quality of sanitation services in Greater Tunis, andpreserve the achievements of the sector; (ii) Promote the reuse of treated wastewater in irrigation on a sustainable basis and insignificant quantities, which is very important given the severity of water scarcity in Tunisia, and (iii) Enhance ONAS performancethrough financial and operational management capacity building.

condition.narrative: Schedule 2, Section I, Article 2: The Borrower shall revise the Environmental Assessment to include the sludge disposal facility(by March 31, 2007), and secure a construction site and financing for this facility accordingly (by June 30, 2008).

Schedule 2, Section V, Article 1: The Borrower shall maintain a ratio of total operating expenses to total operating revenues nothigher than 88.3% for fiscal year ending December 31, 2006; 82.1% for 2007; 81.1% for 2008; 80.4% for 2009; 80.6% for 2010; and76.4% for 2011. A review shall be furnished to the Bank by November 30 in each fiscal year.

Schedule 2, Section V, Article 2: The Borrower shall maintain a ratio of current assets to current liabilities of not less than0.93 for fiscal year ending December 31, 2006; 0.95 for 2007; 0.96 for 2008; 0.95 for 2009; 1.00 for 2010; and 1.00 for 2011. Areview shall be furnished to the Bank by November 30 in each fiscal year.

Schedule 2, Section V, Article 3: The Borrower shall reduce its accounts receivable for sewerage services so that they do notexceed 180 days on December 31, 2006; 160 days for 2007; 140 days for 2008; 130 days for 2009; 120 days for 2010; and 120 days for2011.
